titlestmt.titleproper: A Guide to the Rockefeller Foundation records, Field Staff FA487

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2022-07-01 01:35:23 -0400.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Records more than 20 years old are open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC. Researchers interested in accessing digital media (floppy disks, CDs, DVDs, etc.) or audiovisual material (audio cassettes, VHS, etc.) in this collection must use an access surrogate. The original items may not be accessed because of preservation concerns. To request an access surrogate be made, or if you are unsure if there is an access surrogate, please contact an archivist.

fileplan.head: File Plan
fileplan.p: All material in this collection has not been assigned to a record group within the Rockefeller Foundation archives.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Contains reports, surveys and collected papers from Field Staff of the Rockefeller Foundation, International Health Board/Division, and China Medical Board. Also includes a selection of Officers Actions, Minutes, Board and Program reports and publications.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged in 6 series primarily by Commission/Board, and file type.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Rockefeller Foundation has title, copyright, and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them. Rockefeller Archive Center has authority to grant permission to cite and publish archival material from the collection.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The index includes entries for personal names, organizations, and countries or regions; but not subject terms. Citations to the IHB/D's minutes appear on the right edge of the cards as a 5-digit number, composed of the year and page number. For instance: "25123" = 1925, page 123.

odd.head: General
odd.p: Provides indexing to the International Health Board/Division's (IHB/D) minutes.
